@page "/documentation/github"

<PageTitle>Open Source & Community - XNet› Docs</PageTitle>

<header class="apple-nav">
    <div class="nav-container">
        <a href="/#overview" class="nav-logo">
            <img src="assets/logo.png" width="32" height="32" alt="logo" />
            XNet›
        </a>
        <div class="nav-links">
            <a href="/documentation">Back to Docs</a>
            <a href="/downloads" class="apple-btn-blue text-white">Download <i class="bi bi-chevron-right ms-1 small"></i></a>
        </div>
    </div>
</header>

<main class="container-apple main-page">
    <div class="doc-wrapper">
        <DocSidebar />
        <div class="doc-main-content animate-fade">
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-white mb-4">Community & Open Source</h1>
            <p class="hero-description mb-5">Built by engineers, for engineers. Explore the heart of XNet.</p>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">Our Objective</h2>
                <p class="text-sf-secondary">XNet was born from a simple need: having a robust, professional-grade, and truly native macOS tool for daily network operations. Our goal is to consolidate the dozens of fragmented utilities into a single, high-fidelity experience that engineers can rely on every single day.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">The Development Team</h2>
                <p class="text-sf-secondary">We are a passionate team of network specialized developers and open-source advocates. By combining low-level POSIX knowledge with modern Apple design patterns, we ensure XNet remains the standard for macOS network intelligence.</p>
                <div class="mt-3">
                     <a href="/#team" class="link-blue">Meet the core contributors on our Home page <i class="bi bi-chevron-right small"></i></a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="doc-section mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3 text-white mb-3">How to Contribute</h2>
                <p class="text-sf-secondary mb-4">XNet is and will always be open source. We welcome contributions in many forms:</p>
                <div class="row g-3">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div class="glass-card p-3 text-center h-100">
                            <i class="bi bi-bug h3 text-danger d-block mb-2"></i>
                            <h5 class="text-white h6">Report Bugs</h5>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Found a glitch? Open an issue on GitHub.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div class="glass-card p-3 text-center h-100">
                            <i class="bi bi-code-slash h3 text-primary d-block mb-2"></i>
                            <h5 class="text-white h6">Code Propsal</h5>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Submit Pull Requests for new features.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <div class="glass-card p-3 text-center h-100">
                            <i class="bi bi-translate h3 text-success d-block mb-2"></i>
                            <h5 class="text-white h6">Translation</h5>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Help us localize XNet for everyone.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-5 pt-4 text-center border-top border-dark">
                <h3 class="h5 text-white mb-3">Ready to dive into the code?</h3>
                <a href="https://github.com/kaua-alves-queiros/XNet" target="_blank" class="apple-btn-blue px-5 py-3 fs-5">
                    <i class="bi bi-github me-2"></i> Access the GitHub Repository
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>
